## 1. Android Mobile App Pentesting

### MobSF (Mobile Security Framework — static + dynamic analysis)
```bash
docker run -it -p 8000:8000 opensecurity/mobile-security-framework-mobsf:latest
# Then upload APK via web UI at localhost:8000
```

### jadx (APK decompiler — readable Java source)
```bash
jadx -d output_folder app.apk
jadx-gui app.apk                      # GUI viewer
```

### apktool (you already use this — decompile/rebuild)
```bash
apktool d app.apk -o decompiled_app
apktool b decompiled_app -o rebuilt.apk
```

### Frida (dynamic instrumentation — hook into running app)
```bash
frida-ps -U                                          # list processes on connected device
frida -U -f com.target.app -l script.js --no-pause    # run hook script on app launch
```

### Drozer (Android attack surface analysis)
```bash
drozer console connect
run app.package.list
run app.package.attacksurface com.target.app
```

### adb (Android Debug Bridge — basics)
```bash
adb devices
adb install app.apk
adb shell pm list packages
adb logcat                                            # live device logs
adb pull /data/data/com.target.app/ ./app_data/       # pull app data (rooted device)
```

